LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 350
BY EDUCATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO EDUCATION; AMENDING CHAPTER 10, TITLE 33, IDAHO CODE, BY THE
3 ADDITION OF A NEW SECTION 33-1035, IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE THAT FUNDS
4 DISTRIBUTED BY THE STATE FOR CERTAIN PURPOSES SHALL NOT BE USED FOR
5 OTHER PURPOSES, TO PROVIDE THAT MISUSED FUNDS SHALL BE REIMBURSED TO THE
6 STATE, AND TO PROVIDE FOR A CERTAIN DEDUCTION; AND DECLARING AN EMER-
7 GENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
8 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
9 SECTION 1. That Chapter 10, Title 33, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
10 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
11 ignated as Section 33-1035, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
12 33-1035. BINDING ALLOCATIONS. Any funds distributed by the state to
13 school districts or public charter schools that are specifically identified
14 in statute or in an appropriation bill as intended for a certain purpose
15 shall be used only for such purpose. Any funds intended for a certain pur-
16 pose but used for another purpose shall be reimbursed to the state by the
17 school district or public charter school and deposited to the state general
18 fund. If the school district or public charter school fails to make such
19 reimbursement, an amount equivalent to the misused funds shall be deducted
20 from the state's next payment to the school district or public charter school
21 pursuant to this chapter or chapter 52, title 33, Idaho Code.
22 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
23 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
24 July 1, 2025.

